If you want to Negotiate your Salary like an Expert, you need to give them OPTIONS.⁠
⁠
 This means responding to their offer with a couple of possible compensation packages. ⁠
⁠
 Don't worry - you're not *actually* giving them all of the power - you're simply making them think they're choosing the best scenario for them (but really you'd be happy either way ).⁠
⁠
 And just like that, you've negotiated your ideal package 

𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐨𝐟𝐟 𝐛𝐲 𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐓𝐞𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞:

I've taken the time to reflect on the scope and responsibilities of
the role, as well as what I am uniquely positioned to bring to it (namely, my experience in X and strengths in Y). Considering this,
combined with my international experience, I would be happy with
a package of:⁠

𝐓𝐇𝐄𝐍, 𝐒𝐔𝐆𝐆𝐄𝐒𝐓:

